This article is a transcript of a press briefing by senior administration officials on the topic of Syria. The officials discuss recent actions taken by the US and its allies in response to the Syrian regime's crackdown on its own people. They highlight the calls for President Assad to step aside and the imposition of tough sanctions on the Syrian regime. The officials also mention the coordination with Turkey and other regional allies, as well as the efforts to build international pressure on the Syrian regime. They emphasize that the US does not support military action in Syria and believes that the Syrian people should lead their country's transition. The officials conclude by stating that Assad's days in power are numbered and that the international community is united in calling for him to step aside.